{"title":"How to set up Medical ID in the iPhone Health app for emergencies","link":"https://www.macworld.com/article/2411052/how-to-set-up-medical-id-in-the-iphone-health-app-for-emergencies.html","date":1723107600000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.macworld.com\">Macworld</a></p>\n\n<div>\n<section><div></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>A key advantage of carrying an always-connected device with you is that you can summon help in nearly any emergency. But what if you’re incapacitated? By setting up Medical ID within the Health app in iOS, you can let anyone near you or who discovers you use your phone to send health information to emergency responders or call people you mark as emergency contacts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the Health app, tap your profile picture in the upper-right corner, then tap <em>Medical ID</em>. You can tap <em>Edit</em> to add information about allergies, conditions, medications, and more, as well as adding your blood type and other data.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Scroll down for some additional info you can add: select people from your contacts to add under <em>Emergency Contacts</em>. You can identify their relationship to you when selecting. For greatest safety, enable <em>Show When Locked</em> and <em>Share During Emergency Call</em>.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?w=718\" alt=\"iOS medical ID\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=180%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 180w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=768%2C1283&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=718%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 718w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=919%2C1536&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 919w\" width=\"718\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><p>Consider making it easier for people to help you when you can’t help yourself.</p></figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS medical ID\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=180%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 180w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=768%2C1283&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=718%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 718w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=919%2C1536&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 919w\" width=\"718\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Consider making it easier for people to help you when you can’t help yourself.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS medical ID\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1183w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=180%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 180w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=768%2C1283&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=718%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 718w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-ios-medical-id-setup-bordered.png?resize=919%2C1536&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 919w\" width=\"718\" height=\"1200\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Consider making it easier for people to help you when you can’t help yourself.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div></div>\n\t\t</div></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p>With both enabled, if you are unable to speak or are unconscious, someone can:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Tap your iPhone’s screen or tap its side or home button to reveal the lock screen, tap <em>Emergency</em>, and tap <em>Medical ID</em>.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Press and hold an Apple Watch’s side button, then drag the <em>Medical ID</em> slider to the right.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The second setting lets that person share your Medical ID information from an iPhone or Apple Watch during an emergency call.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With contacts selected, someone can tap <em>Emergency</em> on the lock screen, tap <em>Medical ID</em>, swipe down to <em>Emergency Contacts</em>, and tap any of those numbers to call your contacts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you or someone else uses <a href=\"https://support.apple.com/en-us/104992\">Emergency SOS</a> on your phone to start an emergency call, all the people listed as Emergency Contacts receive a text message after your call with emergency services ends that also contains your current location. They also receive updates as your location changes until you cancel the SOS status.</p>\n\n\n<div><figure><img src=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?w=1146\" alt=\"iOS Medical ID Emergency Contacts\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=287%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 287w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=768%2C804&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=1146%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1146w\" width=\"1146\" height=\"1199\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t<figcaption><p>Tap <em>Medical ID</em> on the Emergency calling screen to reveal medical information and links to call emergency contacts.</p></figcaption>\t\t<div>\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS Medical ID Emergency Contacts\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=287%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 287w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=768%2C804&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=1146%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1146w\" width=\"1146\" height=\"1199\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Tap <em>Medical ID</em> on the Emergency calling screen to reveal medical information and links to call emergency contacts.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div><div><figure><img alt=\"iOS Medical ID Emergency Contacts\" srcset=\"https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?quality=50&amp;strip=all 1200w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=287%2C300&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 287w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=768%2C804&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 768w, https://b2c-contenthub.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/mac911-emergency-calls-sbs.png?resize=1146%2C1200&amp;quality=50&amp;strip=all 1146w\" width=\"1146\" height=\"1199\" loading=\"lazy\" /><figcaption><p>Tap <em>Medical ID</em> on the Emergency calling screen to reveal medical information and links to call emergency contacts.</p></figcaption></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n</div>\n\t\t\t\t<div></div>\n\t\t</div></figure><p>Foundry</p></div>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apple reminds you every four hours for 24 hours that your location is being shared by via a banner in the menu bar. You can tap that banner and tap <em>Stop Sharing Emergency Location</em> to end that form of location sharing.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ask Mac 911</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We’ve compiled a list of the questions we get asked most frequently, along with answers and links to columns: <a href=\"http://www.macworld.com/article/3077986/os-x/your-top-questions-to-mac-911-and-some-answers.html\">read our super FAQ</a> to see if your question is covered. If not, we’re always looking for new problems to solve! Email yours to <a href=\"mailto:mac911@macworld.com\">mac911@macworld.com</a>, including screen captures as appropriate and whether you want your full name used. Not every question will be answered; we don’t reply to emails, and we cannot provide direct troubleshooting advice.</p>\n\n</div>","author":"","siteTitle":"Macworld","siteHash":"37e84dd5a21fa961d6d6630e269546024dbb7741b2e2fadbe74f47383c70dfbb","entryHash":"eba2f2f1e14d986477291aea8a43b6ce67399b08651e3cfda63ccdab19606835","category":"Apple"}